## Step 5.2: Generate HTML Report

**MANDATORY:** After tests pass, create/update the self-contained HTML report.

**File:** `test-results/storybook-test-report.html`

This is a **cumulative** report — each component tested should be added as a tab/section. When generating the report for a new component, preserve existing component sections.

**HTML Report Requirements:**
1. Self-contained single file (no external JS/CSS dependencies)
2. Modern, clean UI with cards, tables, and badges
3. Sections for: Summary stats, Cross-browser results, Detailed timing, Play function steps, Accessibility (Axe), Snapshots, Commands reference, Raw JSON (collapsible)
4. Color-coded badges: green for PASSED, red for FAILED, orange for SKIPPED
5. Component tabs at the top if multiple components are tested
6. Embeds the raw JSON data inline (no external file references)

**HTML Template Structure:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Modus WC — Storybook Test Report</title>
  <style>
    /* Inline CSS: cards, tables, badges, responsive layout */
    /* Color scheme: --primary: #0063a3, --success: #1e8a44, --fail: #da291c */
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Header with overall status badge -->
  <div class="header">
    <h1>Modus WC — Storybook Test Report</h1>
    <span class="overall-badge">[ALL PASSED / X FAILED]</span>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- Summary Cards: Tests Passed, Failed, Browsers, Snapshots, A11y -->
    <!-- Component Tabs (one per component) -->
    <!-- Cross-Browser Results Table -->
    <!-- Detailed Timing Table (per browser per story) -->
    <!-- Play Function Steps Table (numbered steps, per browser) -->
    <!-- Accessibility Axe Audit Table -->
    <!-- Snapshots Table (DOM, ARIA, Visual) -->
    <!-- Commands Reference Block -->
    <!-- Raw JSON (collapsible) -->
  </div>

  <script>
    // Embed raw JSON inline for reference
    const jsonData = { /* test-runner JSON output */ };
    document.getElementById('raw-json').textContent = JSON.stringify(jsonData, null, 2);
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

**Agent Actions:**
1. Parse `test-results/[component-name]-report.json` for data
2. Build HTML from template with real test results
3. If `storybook-test-report.html` already exists with other components, add new component tab
4. Write to `test-results/storybook-test-report.html`

